replies.body:
I think her whole kit is meant to revolve around the whole "I'm a Dragon Born, so I'm tough and powerful!" The problem isn't sustain, it's the simplicity of her kit. With no cc to lock down enemies, there is no fear of her (except for the damage she does), all she does is become a nuisance in fights. If she were to have a rework (which is doubtful for the next year) she would need some form better cc than a weak shove from an ultimate. 

Now it can be said that she is meant to be a split pusher, which is what I think Riot was getting at with Shyvana. A moody dragon woman who has always been an outcast, hence why she isn't so good at team fights, but excels at solo combat and split pushing lanes. With low cc, but higher damage and tank stats to boot, Shyvana can duel a fair number of champions in her human form alone and if needed she can ult to gain more damage and tank to deal with other dueling champions. 

TL:DR Shyvana is a split pushing champion with plenty of damage to do push objectives and duel any champion that comes to stop her lane pushes. I think Riot did a good job with Shyvana, she is not meant to be with her team in fights, but rather pushing objectives on her own. Hope this enlightens you! {{sticker:slayer-pantheon-thumbs}}
